        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "As a non-nix user, I'd like to interject for a moment.\r\n\r\nI don't really see the point of maintaining these files (nix.flake and flake.lock) as part of our repo. Apparently these files are not nearly close to be \"self contained\" in any sense of the word, but depend on hash references to custom specific versions of the Nixpkgs repo. To me this just begs the question: why doesn't these files just _live_ inside these commits of the nixpkgs repo?\r\n\r\nThen changes to these files would be possible to review as PR:s which contain the actual contents of the files, not as inscrutable hashes one need to be blessed with Special Nix Knowledge to know how to figure out what they even mean.\r\n\r\nInterjection over.",
