        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> he Nix team if 100% of this code lives in the Nix repos?\r\n\r\nthe nixpkgs repo makes available but like most official repos, it doesn't provide build instructions for dev versions (you would have twice the number of packages to describe). In that regard \r\n\r\nThe advantage of having the flake directly in the nix repo is that you reference commits directly:\r\n`nix run 'github:neovim/neovim?dir=contrib&rev=242261d4e77806cdb4559c2be58613113a393a4e'`\r\n(or not `nix run 'github:neovim/neovim?dir=contrib` gets latest version). \r\nBut the other aspect I find interesting as well is for development. The flake can get you a development environment with all the dependencies in a manner I find sexier than other approaches (you are in your shell, not a docker image etc). The flake provides differents targets so it can configure the build system with asan, debug symbols etc. \r\n \r\nMy perception is that it doesn't impact the neovim team much since the nix fixes are brought by nix users. Several reports from the nix users have allowed to detect problems with the build system that would  have happened on any distrib.\r\nIf it's a bother to the team let's take the flake down like we took down the deb build, I understand it's not at the core of neovim business.",
