        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "maybe more relevant: \r\nnix can't download arbitrary stuff from the web, it needs a hash for it, which is why you cant have a \"dev\" version in nixpkgs. nixpkgs can not reference \"master\" of neovim, it can only reference specific commits. And bumping the commits daily or even weekly would not be allowed for nixpkgs but this could be done in another repository.it would be sad to lose the ability to build arbitrary neovim commits via the nix cli only (one would need a wrapper script to build in \"pure\"/reproducible mode)",
